# Example

## Repository Interface

```csharp
public interface IEmployeeRepository
{
    string GetEmployeeName(int id);
}
```

---

## Service Class

```csharp
public class EmployeeService
{
    private readonly IEmployeeRepository repository;

    public EmployeeService(
        IEmployeeRepository repository)
    {
        this.repository = repository;
    }

    public string GetName(int id)
    {
        return repository.GetEmployeeName(id);
    }
}
```

---

# Test Using Moq

```csharp
using NUnit.Framework;
using Moq;

[TestFixture]
public class EmployeeServiceTests
{
    [Test]
    public void GetName_ShouldReturnEmployeeName()
    {
        var mockRepo =
            new Mock<IEmployeeRepository>();

        mockRepo
            .Setup(x => x.GetEmployeeName(1))
            .Returns("Raghul");

        EmployeeService service =
            new EmployeeService(mockRepo.Object);

        string result =
            service.GetName(1);

        Assert.AreEqual("Raghul", result);
    }
}
```

---

# Setup()

Defines mock behavior.

```csharp
mock.Setup(x => x.GetEmployeeName(1))
    .Returns("Raghul");
```

Meaning:

```text
If GetEmployeeName(1) is called
Return "Raghul"
```

---

# Verify()

Checks whether method was called.

```csharp
mockRepo.Verify(
x => x.GetEmployeeName(1),
Times.Once
);
```

---

# Verify Example

```csharp
[Test]
public void VerifyMethodCalled()
{
    var mockRepo =
        new Mock<IEmployeeRepository>();

    mockRepo.Setup(x =>
        x.GetEmployeeName(1))
        .Returns("Raghul");

    EmployeeService service =
        new EmployeeService(mockRepo.Object);

    service.GetName(1);

    mockRepo.Verify(
        x => x.GetEmployeeName(1),
        Times.Once
    );
}
```

