# Interview Questions

### What is NUnit?

A unit testing framework for .NET applications.

---

### What is Moq?

A mocking framework used to create fake dependencies for testing.

---

### Why use Moq?

To test business logic without connecting to databases, APIs, or external systems.

---

### Difference between Stub and Mock?

| Stub          | Mock                 |
| ------------- | -------------------- |
| Returns data  | Verifies interaction |
| No validation | Validation supported |

---

### What is Setup()?

Defines expected behavior of a mock object.

```csharp
mock.Setup(x=>x.GetName())
    .Returns("Raghul");
```

---

### What is Verify()?

Checks whether a mocked method was called.

```csharp
mock.Verify(x=>x.GetName(),Times.Once);
```

---

### What is Dependency Injection?

Injecting dependencies through constructor, setter, or interface instead of creating them inside a class.

```csharp
public UserService(IUserRepository repo)
{
    this.repo = repo;
}
```
